<link linkend="GTK-IMAGE-PIXBUF:CAPS"><literal>GTK_IMAGE_PIXBUF</literal></link> (see <link linkend="gtk-status-icon-get-storage-type"><function>gtk_status_icon_get_storage_type()</function></link>).
The caller of this function does not own a reference to the
returned pixbuf.</para>
<para>

</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>status_icon</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> a <link linkend="GtkStatusIcon"><type>GtkStatusIcon</type></link>
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&nbsp;:</term><listitem><simpara> the displayed pixbuf, or <link linkend="NULL:CAPS"><literal>NULL</literal></link> if the image is empty.

</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist><para role="since">Since  2.10
</para></refsect2>
